	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The internal fourscore is mounted on the right side so the turbo and 2/4 switch are accessible.  I pulled the controller sockets off the fourscore board and used them for the top ports.  A big mess of wires connects the original ports to the fourscore, and the fourscore to the nes mobo.  Sometime I will add a hinge to the top of the nes case so it opens well.  I never have any screws there because I take it apart so often.
<br />
<br /><img src="http://www.nesmuseum.com/copyneslcd/fourscore1.png" alt="Image" />
<br /><img src="http://www.nesmuseum.com/copyneslcd/fourscore2.png" alt="Image" />
<br />
<br />Next step:  some neon lights, clear fan covers, racing stripes, rear wing...  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" />

		

